.TH timing_create_clock_use_ideal_slew  22.14 "Fri Oct 06 02:12:27 2023" 
.SH Name \fBtiming_create_clock_use_ideal_slew\fR
.SH Syntax \fBtiming_create_clock_use_ideal_slew\fR   {true | false} 
.P Default: false
.P Enables the use of ideal slew at the inputs of the clock driver cells.
.P When set to true, the software detects created clocks, and uses zero input slew. Other slew values, including those set using set_annotated_transition command, will be ignored.
.P When set to false, the software honors set_annotated_transition command settings.
.P To set this global variable, use the set command.
.P
